fields.physical_description:
Design: cut and folded card board, in the French style with the playing surface printed in colours including gold on one side; the reverse is tan brown; bound on edges with brown tape.
No. of squares: 63
Squares illustrated: all
Square numbering: all
Squares titled: no
Subject of starting square: cyclist
Subject of ending square: goose and policeman
fields.title: le jeu de l'oie; renouvelé des Grecs; Goose game; gänsespiel; ganzenspel.
fields.history_note:
The game has the appearance of a 1930s or 1940s board, however, it is probably a much later copy possibly 1970s as wooden counters and dice have been used.

Left lower corner appears to read - ..00 CHAMBRELENT(or Y * Co PARIS
fields.historical_context_note:
Rewards: forward movement, extra turns and counters
Forfeits: backward movement, missed turns and counters
No. of Players: 5
Equipment required: 36,`1' counters, 17 `2' counters, 12 `5' counters, 6 `10' counters; all printed on sheets of grey card in brown then cut up (very badly)into squares
5 marker discs of wood stained, red, green, brown, black and plain
card board playing surface
original box

Rules:
Rules on the board itself  are in French and there is a German set printed on the inside of the lid.

Squares are:- left lower corner - clown with two geese
